column5: I was wondering if anyone has fished Gullrock Lake ON yet this year? And if someone has could you give me a report. Thanks
Walleye season opens this coming Saturday, the 21st.
Thanks Larry I did not know that

Nipper, I recieved an email from a friend of mine on May 3. He lives in Balmertown and his parents own the camp we go to on Gullrock. He said the ice was all off the lake in mid-April and he thought the walleyes would be all spawned out and back out to the main lake by the opener. He also thought this year will be a very different year for fishing on Gullrock. At least during the spring since the walleyes might be at there mid summer haunts already. Renn
Good, that will spread the boats out a little bit more. Nothing like bumper boat fishing in North West Ontario.
